{"title":"How to watch Il Lombardia 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/il-lombardia-watch","date":1728578348000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/il-lombardia-watch\">How to watch Il Lombardia 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>The last Monument of the season, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/il-lombardia\" target=\"_blank\">Il Lombardia</a>, will take place on Saturday 12th October 2024. Dubbed ‘The Race of the Falling Leaves’ because it is held in autumn, the 252km route will this year start in Bergamo and sees riders scale climbs such as the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/classic-climb-madonna-del-ghisallo\" target=\"_blank\">Madonna del Ghisallo</a> and Colma di Sormano towards Como in Italy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Defending champion <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> will be on the start line and attempting a four-peat of victories.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>How to watch and live stream Il Lombardia 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/GettyImages-1722500518-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 Il Lombardia will be available to watch on <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fget.discoveryplus.com%2Fgb%2Fwatch-entertainment-and-sport%3Futm_medium%3Dsearch%26utm_source%3Dpmax%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjw8MG1BhCoARIsAHxSiQlg0iGYIjmoKvq-9hgG6l1y1G0hfLEkG4B3H3E1q8Q2eTe5LG1uZ5UaAr1XEALw_wcB\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a>. The cheapest plan for the streaming service is £6.99 per month, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. The coverage will take place from 09:25-16:20.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Il Lombardia 2024: Live TV guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Times BST and coverage time and channel subject to change.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 09:25-16:20<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 18:30-20:00 (highlights)<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 20:00-21:30 (highlights)</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cycling-transfer-rumours\">Pro cycling transfers 2024/2025: Elisa Longo Borghini finally confirms move to UAE Team ADQ, Kasper Asgreen signs for EF and Tom Pidcock rumoured to join second-division Q36.5</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/il-lombardia-favourites\">Who are the favourites for Il Lombardia 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/il-lombardia-history\">Pro race history: The legend of the first Il Lombardia in 1905</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n        